Cell.Text: Ah, indeed? The Jarl... Oh yes, he must be referring to my research into the dragons.
Hmm? What? Project? You think you could help me? I really don't think so.

Node.Caption: MQ103FarengarIntroTopic: The Jarl said you had a project you needed help with.

Cell.Text: What? I'm not even... ah, I see. You have some knowledge of the alchemical art.

Node.Caption: MQ103FarengarIntroAlchemy: Hmm. I think you're overheating that Essence of Spriggan Sap...

Cell.Text: What? I never even cast... ah, I see. You have some knowledge of the Higher Art.

Node.Caption: MQ103FarengarIntroMagic: Look out, you're about to step in your own Shock Rune.

Cell.Text: Where? I would never... ah, I see. You are a fellow enchanter.

Node.Caption: MQ103FarengarIntroEnchanting: Isn't it dangerous to leave filled soul gems near an unwarded pentacle?

Cell.Text: [S] Please forgive my earlier rudeness. I am so often interrupted by vistors wandering in, I can occasionally become quite savage. | Now... what did you say you wanted?

Node.Caption: MQ103FarengarIntroMage

Cell.Text: G|The Jarl can be found in the Great Hall, probably sitting on his Jarl's throne. Not over here in a wizard's laboratory.

Node.Caption: MQ103FarengarNeverMind: Never mind. I'll wait for Jarl Balgruuf.

Cell.Text: Straight to the point, eh? No need for tedious how's and why's. I like that. Leave those details to your betters, am I right?

Node.Caption: MQ103FarengarIntroA1: That sounds fun. Where am I going and what am I fetching?

Cell.Text: Ah, no mere brute mercenary, but a thinker - perhaps even a scholar? | You see, when the stories of dragons began to circulate, many dismissed them as mere fantasies, rumors. Impossiblilities. | One sure mark of a fool is to dismiss anything that falls outside his experience as being impossible. | But I began to search for information about dragons - where had they gone all those years ago? And where were they coming from?

Node.Caption: MQ103FarengarIntroA2: What does this have to do with dragons?

Cell.Text: You are eager to begin your adventure. Excellent. The sooner begun, the sooner done, eh?

Node.Caption: MQ103FarengarIntroA3: Just tell me what you need me to do.

Cell.Text: [S] <<Shared>> I, ah, learned of a certain stone tablet said to be housed in Bleak Falls Barrow - a "dragonstone", said to contain a map of dragon burial sites. | Go to Bleak Falls Barrow, find this tablet - no doubt interred in the main chamber - and bring it to me. Simplicity itself.

[S] <<Shared>> I, ah, learned of a certain stone tablet said to be housed in Bleak Falls Barrow - a "dragonstone", said to contain a map of dragon burial sites. | Go to Bleak Falls Barrow, find this tablet - no doubt interred in the main chamber - and bring it to me. Simplicity itself.

Node.Caption: MQ103FarengarIntroB1: So what do you need me to do?

Cell.Text: [S] An old tomb, built by the prehistoric Nords, perhaps dating back to the Dragon War itself. | Ah. Maybe you just want to know how to get there. It's near Riverwood, a miserable little village a few miles south of here. | I'm sure some of the locals can point you in the right direction once you get there.

Node.Caption: MQ103FarengarBleakFallsBarrowTopic: Anything you tell me about Bleak Falls Barrow?

Cell.Text: Well. Must preserve some professional secrets, mustn't we? I have my sources... reliable sources.

Node.Caption: MQ103BleakFallsA1: How do you know this stone tablet is in Bleak Falls Barrow?

Cell.Text: I'm not surprised you've never heard of it. Even I used to think it was just a myth. | But not any more. The Dragon War was a real event, although only the barest glimmer of the actual events has come down to us. | Far back in prehistoric times, the dragons were worshipped as gods in Skyrim. | Many of the monumental ruins that still dot the landscape were in fact built as temples to the dragons. | The details are lost, but at some point the Nords rebelled. After a long and terrible war, the Nords overthrew their dragon overlords.

Node.Caption: MQ103FarengarDragonWarTopic: Tell me more about the Dragon War.

Cell.Text: Oh, no. Many were killed, of course. But many survived into historical times. | Why, this very palace was built by one of Balgruuf's ancestors to hold a captive dragon. Hence its name - Dragonsreach.

Node.Caption: MQ103FarengarDragonWarA1: So were all the dragons killed in the Dragon War?

Cell.Text: Out. She owns the place, she does what she wants.

Node.Caption: MQ103OrgengarInnkeeperTopic: Where's the innkeeper?

Cell.Text: Inn's closed. Bar's still open though. | Feel free to sit and put your head down on the table for as long as you like. I won't bother you.

Node.Caption: MQ103OrgengarInnkeeperA1: So how do I rent a room?

Cell.Text: GS|Bring back this tablet that Farengar wants and I'll be in your debt.
G|That tablet is your priority now. Bring that back from Bleak Falls Barrow and I'm sure we'll have a lot to talk about.
GS|I'll come introduce you to Farengar. He can be a bit difficult. Mages, you know.
G|Farengar can explain the situation better than I can.
G|Farengar is probably puttering around in his lab. Day and night. I'm not sure he ever sleeps.

Node.Caption: MQ103BalgruufBlockingTopic: I need to talk to you.

Cell.Text: [S] Ah! The dragonstone of Bleak Falls Barrow! Seems you are a cut above the usual brutes the Jarl sends my way.

Node.Caption: MQ103FarengarRetrieveBookTopic: I have the stone tablet you wanted.

Cell.Text: You'll have to see the Jarl about that. Maybe his steward Avenicci. I'm sure one of them will pay you appropriately.

Node.Caption: MQ103FarengarRetrieveBookA1: So what about my reward?

Cell.Text: That is where your job ends and mine begins. The work of the mind, sadly undervalued in Skyrim.

Node.Caption: MQ103FarengarRetrieveBookA2: I got you the dragonstone. What next?

Cell.Text: G|My... associate here will be pleased to see your handiwork. She discovered its location, by means she has so far declined to share with me.

Node.Caption: MQ103FarengarRetrieveBookB1

Cell.Text: So the Jarl thinks you can be of use to me? Oh yes, he must be referring to my research into the dragons.

Node.Caption: MQ103FarengarIntroForcegreetTopic

Cell.Text: Yes, I could use someone to fetch something for me. | Well, when I say fetch, I really mean delve into a dangerous ruin in search of an ancient stone tablet that may or may not actually be there.

Node.Caption: MQ103FarengarIntroA0

Cell.Text: [S] Ah! The dragonstone of Bleak Falls Barrow! You already found it! You are cut from a different cloth than the usual brutes the Jarl foists on me.

Node.Caption: MQ103FarengarIntroHaveStone: Oh, do you mean this old stone? (Give Dragonstone to Farengar)
